Architecture

Purpose:
- Public-safe current architecture memory for the MemoryEndpoints.com MATM runtime, companion site, storage boundary, and route surface.

Verification status: active operational memory; verify with the `.uai` audit and route/storage tests before relying on it.
Memory scope: current architecture boundaries, runtime shape, and source-of-truth pointers.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; contains no credential values.
Update route: update this local file when architecture boundaries change; submit durable public-safe architecture summaries to https://memoryendpoints.com/api/matm/memory-events/submit when authenticated.
Source of truth: `memoryendpoints/`, tests, deployment/runtime contracts, and database-backed MemoryEndpoints.com wiki records. Existing `docs/` files are transitional migration/evidence material until their knowledge is deliberately moved into MemoryEndpoints.com.
Next action for agents: preserve the product boundary and verify route/storage behavior before expanding claims.
Must not expose: raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, private handoff payloads, raw one-time keys, or private deployment values.

Current architecture state:
- MemoryEndpoints.com is the real MATM product/API surface.
- MultiAgentMemory.com is the static companion documentation site inside `sites/multiagentmemory.com/`.
- Runtime code stays pure Python standard library WSGI, with browser-native HTML/CSS/JavaScript assets.
- Public discovery and evidence routes are implemented in `memoryendpoints/app.py` and `memoryendpoints/site_data.py`.
- Protected MATM routes cover workspace status, agent registration, memory submit/search, review queue, current messages, inbox, notification acknowledgement, redacted receipts, and redacted audit-log readback.
- Protected UAIX active-memory routes support one narrow full-package exception for an `accountless_browser_ai` with no durable local filesystem. Packages bind to a workspace key and registered agent, store date-free structured public-safe virtual records with immutable revisions, and derive startup readiness from required roles.
- Normal filesystem agents keep local `.uai` bodies local. `matm_uai_collaboration_heads` and `matm_uai_edit_claims` store only real project, logical path, SHA-256 head, bounded owner lease, and public-safe intent/completion metadata so simultaneous agents can detect overlap and stale copies.
- A virtual `.uai/short-term-memory.uai` logical record creates no local file and does not weaken the actual-local-filename ban. A collaboration claim is not an operating-system lock, content replication, or automatic merge.
- Protected knowledge wiki routes cover project upsert/list, database-backed company/workspace/project tree retrieval, and one-document wiki indexing through `matm_crawl_sources` and `matm_search_documents`.
- Reviewed report ingestion preserves one canonical source record and can create multiple semantically bounded knowledge pages from that source. Each page has independent title, description, keywords, hierarchy placement, route, content hash, and source-line provenance.
- Reviewer-authored overlays may supply a corrected current synthesis while the original source and selected-source hashes remain intact. Overlay metadata records its content hash, declares that no local overlay path is stored, and keeps the complete historical source available as protected evidence.
- Report section selection matches human-visible Markdown headings by normalizing backslash-escaped punctuation while preserving the exact raw source section and line provenance in stored content.
- Report section discovery ignores ATX-looking text inside fenced or indented code blocks so example payload headings cannot split a source into false knowledge pages.
- An explicit stop heading may span unfenced embedded Markdown-document headings when a report example would otherwise look like a false peer section; the reviewer-supplied boundary and exact line range remain auditable.
- Knowledge lifecycle is first-class: `knowledgeStatus`, `authorityLevel`, `statusReason`, and `supersededByDocumentId` distinguish current canonical guidance from proposed, historical, superseded, archived, community, or unverified material. Search exposes relevance separately from lifecycle ranking and prefers current canonical guidance.
- External web links are first-class `matm_external_links` records, not text-only URL fragments. `matm_external_link_mentions` provides many-to-many citation context between canonical links and knowledge pages.
- Report provenance belongs to each `matm_external_link_mentions` row through `source_report_name`, not to mutable canonical-link metadata. One canonical URL may therefore retain distinct source-report, relationship, context, and page provenance for every citation without the latest report overwriting earlier evidence.
- `/api/matm/internet-search` and `/api/matm/external-links` search reviewed URL, host, site name, page title, description, keywords, crawl/review state, and citing-page context. Link indexing does not automatically fetch or execute the target.
- Discoverability audits preserve report-time availability claims as historical evidence and record fresh reachability separately. A timeout, crawler label, impossible bibliography date, or missing body cannot prove a WAF cause or current outage; current claims require status, effective URL, headers, media type, parse result, and environment evidence.
- Public HTML, crawler policy, sitemaps, LLM orientation, custom manifests, OpenAPI, optional protocol adapters, and protected runtime behavior should express equivalent truth without identical payload size. Public representation parity never publishes tenant titles, identifiers, deep routes, source prefixes, or full protected context.
- Single-link ingestion canonicalizes language tags, content types, and crawl-policy slugs before fingerprinting and readback so storage normalization cannot produce a false verification failure.
- Canonical external-link review state is workspace-wide. Adding an incidental `unreviewed` citation preserves an existing explicit `reviewed`, `quarantined`, or `rejected` disposition; a deliberate non-default review request remains the transition mechanism.
- Canonical external-link search keywords are cumulative across reviewed upserts. Storage and the single-link client preserve existing casing and order, append only case-insensitively new terms, and verify the effective union so a later report cannot erase earlier retrieval vocabulary.
- Single-memory review consumes one memory event or one ingestion report, validates the current review state and firewall decision, applies one idempotent promote/reject/quarantine decision, stores only a review-note hash in local evidence, and verifies the resulting protected queue record. Do not replace this with source-specific batch promotion or shell-only review mutations.
- The human `/knowledge` route is an empty authentication shell, not a public wiki. It must render no tree, page, search result, or external-link record until a workspace key succeeds, and it must clear previously rendered private data before re-authentication or after an authorization failure.
- The authenticated human wiki and AI swarm knowledge routes read the same tenant-isolated database records. Workspace keys are bound to one workspace and cannot select another workspace; account/user identities have many-to-many company memberships but no account/user-owned knowledge scope.
- Protected memory search keeps exact structured identifiers and scope/lifecycle filters authoritative while ranking conceptual text with stem-aware terms and normalized storage-size units. When a memory source resolves to a protected wiki page, search may augment relevance and readback with that page's title, description, keywords, taxonomy, and reviewed text; the linked knowledge remains separately identified and never changes review or promotion state implicitly.
- The authenticated human wiki keeps the active article and active search results ahead of the taxonomy tree on narrow screens, bounds the mobile tree viewport, and retains the three-pane taxonomy/article/results layout on desktop. A protected deep link focuses and reveals its requested article after authentication without exposing it in the signed-out shell.
- Durable wiki scope is limited to company, workspace, and project. Do not create generated filesystem wiki trees or user/account/goal/task durable knowledge trees as a source of truth.
- Goal and task memory and meeting rooms coordinate active work but do not create durable crawlable wiki ownership. Promote lasting findings to the narrowest company, workspace, or project scope before the transient coordination context ends.
- Single-report evidence files structurally redact company, workspace, project, and scope values from returned query URLs and fail their own success gate if a credential or raw scope identifier survives report serialization.
- `docs/` must not become a permanent knowledge store. After its knowledge is reviewed and moved one item at a time into the database-backed wiki/memory system, the repository should no longer retain `docs/` as a parallel documentation hierarchy.
- Stdlib SQLite is the default unconfigured local backend and uses normalized MATM tables rather than a JSON document store.
- Local dogfood explicitly uses an isolated SQLite database and restores inherited file, SQLite, and backend environment values before live work; it must not inherit a production MySQL profile or use the obsolete JSON-store path as its relational test target.
- Production MemoryEndpoints.com uses the verified MySQL/MariaDB backend. Production claims still require current route and backend verification evidence.
- The JSON file adapter is explicit test/parity infrastructure only; it is not the default or the durable knowledge source of truth.
